items.title: Investing in America 2025
items.summary: Google’s deep investments in American technical infrastructure, R&D and the workforce will help the U.S. continue to lead the world in AI, Google says . Google's deep investments will help American tech companies continue to develop and compete in artificial intelligence, the company said in a new blog post on Monday . Google says it is investing in the American workforce and infrastructure to develop AI technology .

items.title: New ways to plan travel with AI in Search
items.summary: AI Mode search bar can help you plan a trip with the help of AI Mode . AI Mode searches can also be used to help people plan their travel plans . The search bar is a result of the AI Mode feature that lets users plan their own trips with AI Mode enabled to search for travel destinations in AI Mode mode . For more information, visit CNN.com/Travel.com and iReport .

items.title: Google is committing $2.25 million to support AI-ready data in Africa.
items.summary: New funding from Google will help launch a regional Data Commons for Africa . New funding will help create a regional data Commons for African countries . Google says it will help build a data Commons in Africa for African nations . Google: Africa's Data Commons will be a Data Commons in the region, Africa's biggest source of data and source of information .

items.title: Human-centric IAM is failing: Agentic AI requires a new identity control plane
items.summary: Traditional identity and access management (IAM) designed for humans breaks at agentic scale . Each AI agent must be treated as a first-class citizen within your identity ecosystem . A single over-permissioned agent can exfiltrate data or trigger erroneous business processes at machine speed . Use synthetic data to prove value, then earn the right to touch the real thing .

items.title: Google’s new AI training method helps small models tackle complex reasoning
items.summary: Researchers at Google Cloud and UCLA have proposed a new reinforcement learning framework that significantly improves the ability of language models to learn challenging multi-step reasoning tasks . SRL reformulates problem-solving as a sequence of logical “actions,” providing rich learning signals during the training process . This approach enables smaller models to . learn complex problems that were previously out of reach for other common training techniques .

items.title: ChatGPT Group Chats are here … but not for everyone (yet)
items.summary: ChatGPT now offers Group Chats, allowing multiple users to join the same, single ChatGpt conversation . The feature is only available as a limited pilot for now to users in Japan, New Zealand, South Korea, and Taiwan (all tiers, including free usage). The move follows Microsoft's Copilot AI assistant and Anthropic's Anthropic AI assistant .

items.title: OpenAI experiment finds that sparse models could give AI builders the tools to debug neural networks
items.summary: OpenAI researchers are experimenting with a new approach to designing neural networks . The aim of making AI models easier to understand, debug, and govern . Sparse models can provide enterprises with a better understanding of how these models make decisions . The company defines interpretability as “methods that help us understand why a model produced a given output”
